  "course_description": "Close analysis of poetic forms using a variety of approaches. Focuses on literary, cultural, or historical interpretations of selected poems from the Middle Ages to contemporary experiments and on the act and art of reading. Includes attention to form, content, and context.",
  "course_notes": "As a 300-level course within the series Widerstand und Anpassung (Resistance and Conformity), German 332 approaches modern German poetry as a dynamic field of aesthetic expression shaped by tension between innovation and constraint. Covering roughly 250 years of poetic production, the course follows a combined chronological and genre-based structure to trace how German-speaking authors have responded - whether through resistance or conformity - to poetic conventions and broader societal, cultural, and political pressures. At its core, the course is guided by three interrelated trajectories: (1) language and form, (2) thematic and historical context, and (3) independent scholarly engagement.",
